    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Suicidal Secrets</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marilyn Brookwood letter comments on April 1 Ethicist column commenting on letter from teacher to whom student confided having suicidal thoughts</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>There can be no secrets when an adolescent in a school shares with an adult that he or she is considering suicide (The Ethicist, April 1). School personnel are ethically obliged to report such communications to clinical and administrative parties. And, most important, parents must be informed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>There can be no secrets when an adolescent in a school shares with an adult that he or she is considering suicide (The Ethicist, April 1). School personnel are ethically obliged to report such communications to clinical and administrative parties. And, most important, parents must be informed.</p>
        <p>The teacher was derelict in trying to handle the situation alone. Confidences cannot be kept when a life is at stake. The student may get angry at a broken promise, but will be alive to talk about it.</p>
        <p>Marilyn Brookwood</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
